<p>I have a Controler1 that sends an event on button click:</p>  <pre><code>$rootScope.$broadcast('Click'); </code></pre>  <p>Then I'm catching this event in Controller2 and updating a list of orders:</p>  <pre><code>$scope.$on('Click', function() {     console.log("Somebody clicked the button");     $scope.showingOrders = Order.getMyOrders(); }); </code></pre>  <p>where Order.getMyOrders() sends a request to server for a list of orders.</p>  <p>Controller2 controls this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div class="list-group"&gt;     &lt;a href="#/dashboard" id="{{order.id}}"          data-toggle="modal"          data-target="#showOrderModal"         class="list-group-item"         ng-click="setClickedOrder(showingOrders[$index])"         ng-repeat="order in showingOrders | orderBy : '-id'"&gt;         &lt;h4 class="list-group-item-heading"&gt;            Order â„–{{order.id}} from {{order.owner.fullName}}         &lt;/h4&gt;         p class="list-group-item-text"&gt;{{order.description}}&lt;/p&gt;     &lt;/a&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p>What am I getting:</p>  <ul> <li>By the first click "Somebody clicked the button" is showing in console, but the list of orders is not redrawing</li> <li>By the next clicks an order list redraws, but always the last order isn't showing</li> </ul>  <p>The code for Order.getMyOrders():</p>  <pre><code>app.factory('Order', ['$resource', function($resource) {     return $resource(BASE_PATH + ORDER_PATH, {}, {         get: {url: BASE_PATH + ORDER_PATH + '/:orderId', method: 'GET', params: {orderId: '@orderId'}},         create: {method: 'POST'},         getNearMe: {url: BASE_PATH + ORDER_PATH + '/near', method: 'GET',             params: {latitude: '', longitude: ''}, isArray: true},         getDoneOrders: {url: BASE_PATH + ORDER_PATH + '/done', method: 'GET',             params: {latitude: '', longitude: ''}},         getMyOrders: {method: 'GET', isArray: true}     }); </code></pre>  <p>What am I doing wrong? Can I do this in another way?</p>